prompt:
Add auto-rebuild on push to main using github-relay.

## Context
cosmo is a NixOS flake that manages multiple hosts. classic-laddie already runs github-relay (a webhook router) on port 8077 with Tailscale Funnel. Currently it only forwards events to Klaus. We want to add a consumer that triggers a NixOS rebuild when cosmo's main branch is updated.

## What to change

### 1. Add cosmo-rebuild consumer to github-relay config
In hosts/classic-laddie/default.nix, the github-relay consumers are defined around line 149-172. Add a new consumer:

```nix
cosmo-rebuild = {
  repo = "patflynn/cosmo";
  events = [ "push" ];
  branches = [ "main" ];
  action = "systemd";
  unit = "cosmo-rebuild";
};
```

Keep the existing klaus consumer unchanged.

### 2. Create a cosmo-rebuild systemd service
In hosts/classic-laddie/default.nix (or a new module if cleaner), add a systemd oneshot service:

```nix
systemd.services.cosmo-rebuild = {
  description = "Rebuild NixOS from cosmo main";
  serviceConfig = {
    Type = "oneshot";
    # Run as root since nixos-rebuild needs it
  };
  path = with pkgs; [ git nixos-rebuild nix ];
  script = ''
    # Rebuild directly from GitHub, no local clone needed
    nixos-rebuild switch --no-write-lock-file --refresh --flake github:patflynn/cosmo#classic-laddie
  '';
};
```

Key considerations:
- Use `--flake github:patflynn/cosmo#classic-laddie` to pull directly from GitHub (no need to maintain a local clone)
- Use `--no-write-lock-file` since we're building from a remote flake
- Use `--refresh` to ensure nix fetches the latest commit
- The service runs as root by default (systemd), which is needed for nixos-rebuild
- Add a 10-minute timeout (TimeoutStartSec=600) so a broken build doesn't hang forever
- Add a rate limit so rapid pushes don't pile up rebuilds — consider adding StartLimitIntervalSec=300 and StartLimitBurst=3
- Make sure the service has network access (no network sandboxing)

### 3. Ensure the webhook is configured on GitHub
Add a note in the PR description that the GitHub webhook for patflynn/cosmo needs to be configured to point at the Tailscale Funnel URL if not already done. (The relay URL is https://classic-laddie.coin-inconnu.ts.net)

## Constraints
- Keep changes minimal — only add the consumer and the systemd service
- Don't modify the existing klaus consumer
- Run nixfmt on any changed files
- Run nix flake check if possible (may not work in the worktree without the full system)
- Make sure the systemd service has sensible defaults (restart limits, timeouts, logging)
